    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1887-03-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1887-03-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="587" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d587">
                <head>No. 587.<lb/>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Bayard</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Lothrop</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1887-03-23">
                            <hi rend="italic">March</hi> 23,
                            1887</date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 78.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I reply to your No. 100, concerning the
                        confiscation of the two schooners, <hi rend="italic">Eiza</hi> and <hi rend="italic">Henrietta</hi> (the subject of recent instructions), by
                        the Russian authorities, that the Department will hold the cases under
                        consideration and await further reports.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">T. F. Bayard.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
